<i>[Episode 11]</i>

16
00:01:35,110 --> 00:01:37,370
She's still in a coma.

17
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:40,190
Please Andriana,

18
00:01:40,190 --> 00:01:42,570
I need to know the truth.

19
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:56,560
Miss.

20
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:01,810
Leave us, I'll stay with her.

21
00:02:36,770 --> 00:02:40,210
I just called Aunt Andriana.

22
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,690
She told me a lot of things.

23
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,680
I always hated you.

24
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:53,970
You can't imagine how it was

25
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:57,230
for a ten year old child to be sent to a foreign country,

26
00:02:57,230 --> 00:03:01,080
and to live with a foreign family.

27
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,200
I was so scared.

28
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:11,920
I know,

29
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:15,920
Andriana is one of your best friends.

30
00:03:16,570 --> 00:03:18,640
But she isn't my friend.

31
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:21,190
She is not my family.

32
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:23,630
She isn't my mother.

33
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,940
I still remember,

34
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:31,810
every day and every night in England

35
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:34,240
I missed you.

36
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:40,970
I was waiting for the day you would come to take me home.

37
00:03:43,580 --> 00:03:47,280
But every day I would be disapointed.

38
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:52,050
Finally I realized,

39
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:54,530
that you would never come.

40
00:03:55,240 --> 00:04:00,200
You sent me abroad to take revenge on my dad.

41
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:03,380
I was just a pawn in your plan.

42
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:07,540
Since then,

43
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:10,890
I started to hate you.

44
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:15,870
I didn't take your calls, and I didn't even want to see you.

45
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:21,320
If anyone even mentioned your name, I would get mad.

46
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:24,220
But not long after, you started to feel regret.

47
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:27,680
You said you'd take me home.

48
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:33,520
But at that time, I felt like I could never

49
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:37,490
forgive the mother who abandoned me.

50
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:46,050
I told you, if you tried to come to England to find me

51
00:04:46,050 --> 00:04:50,160
I would leave home, so that none of you could find me.

52
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:58,120
You've probably forgotten all that.

53
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:04,090
These past years, just like you,

54
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:07,150
I was living with pain and hate.

55
00:05:09,780 --> 00:05:14,360
I thought I meant nothing to you.

56
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:18,500
Until I saw those photos.

57
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:24,030
I realized, things weren't as I thought.

58
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:29,690
For so many years, you had been by my side.

59
00:05:31,410 --> 00:05:35,120
My mom loved me so much.

60
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,710
I was so happy.

61
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:48,360
But when I came to see you,

62
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:51,160
you said all those things to me.

63
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:57,230
Doctor Bai said you did it

64
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:59,830
because you didn't want to be a burden on me.

65
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:02,470
You wanted me to hate you, forget you,

66
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:05,210
and start a new life.

67
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:20,670
But after so many years,

68
00:06:22,410 --> 00:06:24,850
I can't do it.

69
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,180
Xiao Xuan.

70
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,670
Mom.

71
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,350
Xuan.

72
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:00,440
<i>[EICU]</i>

73
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,660
So touching.

74
00:07:02,660 --> 00:07:04,130
If only it hadn't taken so long.

75
00:07:04,130 --> 00:07:06,160
We've got the new laboratory.

76
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,520
I'll soon be back to working in cardiac surgery.

77
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,050
Can you be humane at all?

78
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:16,450
Going back to cardiac surgery and saving many patients is the most humane thing ever.

79
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:21,060
Doctor Bai said that you can have surgery in two days time.

80
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:29,700
Ms Ge, here are your documents.

81
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:42,050
I signed it.

82
00:07:42,050 --> 00:07:44,560
Give it to your father.

83
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,200
Alright.

84
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:52,880
Doctor Bai was right.

85
00:07:53,810 --> 00:07:56,810
People can't live in hate.

86
00:07:57,670 --> 00:08:01,190
I've made him suffer enough over the years.

87
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:03,880
And hurt myself in the process.

88
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,790
I need to put an end to it.

89
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:11,390
He'll be free and I'll be free too.

90
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:20,490
I'll take care of you.

91
00:08:28,050 --> 00:08:30,610
- You've done all the checks? 
 - Yes.

92
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:35,100
Prepare the instruments.

93
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,260
<i>[Operating Room]<i></i></i>

94
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:21,900
- Mom. 
 - Xiao Xuan.

95
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:24,770
The surgery was a success, how are you feeling?

96
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:27,210
We were able to completely remove the tumor.

97
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:29,470
At the moment, we can't see any remaining cancer cells.

98
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:34,220
Remember, you must come back for a check-up every three months to prevent a relapse.

99
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:39,440
Isn't it time to say thank you?

100
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:46,490
Thank you, Doctor Bai.

101
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:54,450
And thank you, Doctor Xu.

102
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:56,190
You're welcome.

103
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,570
Doctor Xu!

104
00:10:03,570 --> 00:10:06,440
You know, you aren't my type.

105
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:11,040
But...I didn't mean it when I said Doctor Bai was more handsome than you.

106
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,490
Thank you.

107
00:10:29,180 --> 00:10:30,990
This face...

108
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:35,960
is really too good-looking.

109
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:44,980
Thank you.

110
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:48,330
If it wasn't for you, Ge Hong wouldn't have agreed to the surgery so quickly.

111
00:10:48,330 --> 00:10:50,880
Colleagues help one another out.

112
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:54,020
You helped me with Fang Nan.

113
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:02,120
How did you know that Ge Hong was hiding something?

114
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:06,050
I remembered that when I was working with Doctors Without Borders,

115
00:11:06,050 --> 00:11:08,590
I treated a pregnant woman.

116
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:11,810
Before I gave her anesthesia, she kept stressing to me

117
00:11:11,810 --> 00:11:13,840
that we couldn't remove her uterus.

118
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,860
She was willing to die instead.

119
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:19,150
I didn't understand at the time.

120
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:21,540
But later, I found out that over there,

121
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:23,240
a woman who's unable to give birth to children

122
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:25,820
loses all her dignity.

123
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:28,510
So I realized that if Ge Hong was unwilling to have the surgery,

124
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:31,110
she must have her reasons.

125
00:11:31,110 --> 00:11:35,110
That's also why you insisted on respecting

126
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:36,350
Wang Qing's personal wishes, right?

127
00:11:36,350 --> 00:11:39,800
I believe that doctors not only deal with illness

128
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,320
but also with the person behind the illness.

129
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,510
Study of humans.

130
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:49,020
Perhaps there are some contradictions with the medicine that you believe in.

131
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:51,040
That's true,

132
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:53,690
but things aren't that absolute either, right?

133
00:11:53,690 --> 00:11:55,820
I can agree with that.

134
00:11:59,550 --> 00:12:02,440
I hope we can work together in the future.

135
00:12:17,780 --> 00:12:19,340
Professor!

136
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:21,170
What are you doing here?

137
00:12:21,930 --> 00:12:23,110
You gave me a fright.

138
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:24,090
I was waiting for you.

139
00:12:24,090 --> 00:12:26,420
You can talk to me during the day in my office.

140
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:28,860
Why were you waiting here? What's going on?

141
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:32,330
You're never in your office when I visit. I had to come wait here.

142
00:12:32,330 --> 00:12:33,840
So, what do you want to say?

143
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:38,190
Sir, Ge Hong has made a donation.

144
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:42,410
The hospital laboratory is set now. Shouldn't I be returning to the cardiothoracic department?

145
00:12:42,410 --> 00:12:43,870
How are those two things related?

146
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:45,370
Of course they're related.

147
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:48,190
If I hadn't persisted, Ge Hong wouldn't have agreed to the surgery.

148
00:12:48,190 --> 00:12:51,390
You're her primary doctor. Convincing her to have the surgery

149
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:53,180
is simply a part of your job.

150
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:55,820
- But... 
- That's enough.

151
00:13:03,530 --> 00:13:05,060
Hey.

152
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,540
What are you doing?

153
00:13:07,540 --> 00:13:09,680
You even put your seat belt on.

154
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,550
Alright, stop messing around.

155
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:14,010
My wife is waiting for me to have dinner.

156
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:18,140
That's perfect. If you won't agree, then I'll go home with you.

157
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:21,910
I'll just live there and eat there from now on.

158
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:23,610
How old are you? Tell me.

159
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:25,390
How old are you?

160
00:13:25,390 --> 00:13:27,510
You're still acting so shamelessly.

161
00:13:28,570 --> 00:13:31,130
You forced me to do this.

162
00:13:31,130 --> 00:13:33,400
Okay, fine. Come home with me.

163
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:37,540
My wife has been wanting to find you a partner.

164
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:41,300
She knows some girls who are quite nice. You should meet them.

165
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,000
Why don't I invite a few over tonight?

166
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,660
Your wife truly has great taste.

167
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:49,450
What did you just say?

168
00:13:49,450 --> 00:13:53,380
My wife's taste... What about it?

169
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,580
Are you saying that I'm not handsome?

170
00:13:58,580 --> 00:14:02,830
No. You're the most handsome teacher I've ever had.

171
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:06,190
Sir, look over there.

172
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:09,250
You rotten kid!

173
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:21,380
Doctor, Xiao Ting's stomach hurt a lot during class today.

174
00:14:21,380 --> 00:14:23,810
We were excused from class so I could take her to the hospital.

175
00:14:23,810 --> 00:14:25,300
How long has it been hurting?

176
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:28,130
For about two hours today.

177
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:30,560
Have you had stomach pain before?

178
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,050
For the past two years, it comes and goes.

179
00:14:33,050 --> 00:14:36,620
It would hurt for a few days and then get better, so I never paid much attention.

180
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:38,860
But this month, the pain is a lot more frequent.

181
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:41,130
And it's especially painful today.

182
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:46,190
70/40, your blood pressure's low. Lie down over there.

183
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:58,520
Relax.

184
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:00,150
Hands.

185
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,960
It hurts here, right?

186
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:12,240
Tenderness on the lower right abdomen.

187
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:15,960
No rebound tenderness. It could be acute appendicitis.

188
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:19,350
Is your period regular?

189
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:27,020
Doctor, my period has always been irregular.

190
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:31,120
You're her boyfriend, right?

191
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,640
Yes.

192
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:35,420
I'm going to give you a urine test.

193
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:36,720
A urine test?

194
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:39,680
To see if you're pregnant.

195
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,530
I'm well aware of my body's condition.

196
00:15:41,530 --> 00:15:44,010
I'm not pregnant. I don't want the test.

197
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:46,340
A urine test is routine practice.

198
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:49,120
After the results come out, we can continue assessing.

199
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,130
I'm not doing it. Wang Xiang, let's go.

200
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:55,300
You can't leave yet. You have abdominal pain and low blood pressure.

201
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,630
- Are you okay? 
- Are you okay?

202
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:03,580
Tang Hua, get the patient a blood test.

203
00:16:03,580 --> 00:16:07,000
Since the patient has denied being pregnant, also get her a CT scan.

204
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,670
Make sure she signs the waiver first.

205
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:11,120
Okay.

206
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,880
Let's go. Come this way.

207
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:15,380
Slowly.

208
00:16:18,650 --> 00:16:20,720
How's the pain now?

209
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:25,160
The CT shows no swelling or presence of exudate in the appendix,

210
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,560
no deposits in the urinary system,

211
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,490
a small amount of fluid in the pelvic cavity.

212
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:34,020
Imaging is unclear, and ectopic pregnancy can't be ruled out.

213
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:38,200
I want to speak with you privately.

214
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:42,450
Wang Xiang, it's been a long day. I'm kind of hungry.

215
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:44,170
Can you buy me something to eat?

216
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,660
Okay.

217
00:16:51,930 --> 00:16:56,600
Dr. Xiao, you want to convince me to take a pregnancy test, don't you?

218
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:59,810
The sooner we test, the sooner we can eliminate different causes for illness.

219
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:02,320
We can only treat you once we determine the cause of the problem.

220
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:07,600
Dr. Xiao, do you know why I'm unwilling to be tested?

221
00:17:10,890 --> 00:17:13,110
My whole life,

222
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:19,490
I've always been the kid parents compare their own kids to.

223
00:17:19,490 --> 00:17:24,900
Throughout school, I was always a top student and brought home many awards.

224
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:28,330
When I got to college, I started getting scholarships.

225
00:17:28,330 --> 00:17:30,440
And yet,

226
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:33,570
my parents have no confidence in me.

227
00:17:33,570 --> 00:17:38,300
Whenever I go home for the holidays, my parents talk to me like they're questioning a prisoner.

228
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:42,780
Now I have a boyfriend and I've kept it a secret from them.

229
00:17:42,780 --> 00:17:46,440
I'm done living as someone untrustworthy.

230
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:51,110
I'm sure that your parents love you, even if their method is wrong.

231
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:55,930
You should find an opportunity to talk it out with them.

232
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:57,920
It's pointless.

233
00:17:57,920 --> 00:18:00,730
Yu Ya Ting's blood test came back.

234
00:18:00,730 --> 00:18:06,220
Her blood amylase levels are normal, and acute pancreatitis is unlikely.

235
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:08,060
Okay.

236
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:11,020
She still hasn't agreed.

237
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:14,550
She's being too stubborn. The testing is for her own good.

238
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:17,780
Although we're trying to treat patients,

239
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:20,550
we have to respect their personal wishes.

240
00:18:24,630 --> 00:18:27,980
Lift your legs. Let me do an examination.

241
00:18:35,730 --> 00:18:38,420
- Does this hurt? 
- A little.

242
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:42,460
Tenderness on the lower right abdomen,

243
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:46,010
but there's no tightness in the stomach. The CT shows no problems.

244
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:50,180
Further testing should be done where the imaging is unclear.

245
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:54,500
Oh, right, have you done a pregnancy test and ultrasound yet?

246
00:18:55,960 --> 00:19:00,820
You should get it done to rule out an ectopic pregnancy.

247
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:05,840
I'll transfer you over to the EICU first.

248
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:24,350
Dr. Xiao,

249
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:27,890
I think you should try to convince Yu Ya Ting again.

250
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,750
I know you've already spoken to her,

251
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:35,290
and I trust your professional judgement.

252
00:19:35,290 --> 00:19:39,750
But trusting her and getting the test done don't conflict with each other.

253
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:44,360
It's a necessary test in the diagnostic process.

254
00:19:50,670 --> 00:19:53,960
I understand what you're saying,

255
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:59,210
but it might be difficult for a young woman to open up about these kinds of matters.

256
00:19:59,210 --> 00:20:01,450
You have to understand that too.

257
00:20:02,730 --> 00:20:05,430
I'll find another opportunity to talk to her.

